caption: Was reading through some of the reviews and would agree with allot of them! There's tons of musical history and entertainment history as well. Personally the place reminds me of a punk rock type of bar with a Portland, Oregon feel to it or a grunge look. Usually have specials on drinks too.
The best music venue downtown!
Sticky floors, check. Great music, check. Friendly staff, check. Simply put, the best dive bar on planet Earth.

pro tip: if you are hosting a concert in July please invest in AC for the venue or have a sign that warns customers of the lack of AC upstairs. it was so hot that it someone breathing on me was refreshing... yikes I go to concerts all the time and this is definitely the worst venue I have been to in terms of air temperature.

Gabe's had a rocking feel to it.  I didn't see much of the main floor/bar, but it looked well taken care of, but still had the grunge feel/look going on. I recently attended Lady Lamb the Beekeeper's show at Gabe's. It was a great show with nice ambience and decent sound and acoustics. Now that may just be because her guitar playing is wonderful, but Gabe's certainly didn't retract from the experience. BUT My only complaint is when Torres took the stage their set was nearly ruined by a band playing on the main floor of Gabe's. It did not make sense to me why they would schedule another band at the same time as the "headliner" (Torres) it severely subtracted from the experience. All-in-all Gabe's is a good "venue" for a vast selection of genres and tastes and I plan on coming back for more shows!
